1
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:18,067
Red, I don't understand.
I thought they saw us!

2
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:19,700
Why didn't they stop for us?

3
00:00:19,767 --> 00:00:21,200
We still have a chance.

4
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:23,833
What is this
murderer doing here?

5
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:26,500
I'm here to find my daughter.

6
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:29,367
Is she one of the passengers
of the plane that crashed?

7
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:31,767
Do you know anyone
from that flight too?

8
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:34,467
I'm so sorry, everyone.

9
00:00:34,567 --> 00:00:38,633
We don't have a new update
about the investigation.

10
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:39,433
What?

11
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:40,967
You people are
incompetent!

12
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:41,767
You're all stupid!
Dumb!

13
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:43,233
That's enough!

14
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:44,500
Stop!

15
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:45,733
Just leave her be!

16
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,667
Let go of me!

17
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:49,533
Yen, please!

18
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:54,400
I don't want us to
die on this island.

19
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:55,567
But we'll end
up dead anyway.

20
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:57,733
We almost die out
there on the sea.

21
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:59,767
Coach taught us a lot
of things, remember?

22
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:05,533
Yen, we may have failed,
but we can keep on trying.

23
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:10,000
First thing in the morning,
you'll see my old self.

24
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:14,000
We'll work together to
get out of this island.

25
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:42,467
Sorry, I'm a little heavy.

26
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:44,700
Are you okay?

27
00:01:49,267 --> 00:01:51,200
Red, you're bleeding!

28
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:53,233
I landed on something
sharp when we fell.

29
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:55,267
Come on, let's go
back to the shelter.

30
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:56,633
We'll clean that up.

31
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:58,000
Put your arms around me.

32
00:01:58,067 --> 00:01:59,033
I'm okay.

33
00:01:59,100 --> 00:01:59,700
Can you walk?

34
00:01:59,767 --> 00:02:00,933
Yeah.

35
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:27,367
Luckily we kept this extra
cloth from my dress.

36
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:36,933
Your wound should
be exposed.

37
00:02:37,733 --> 00:02:42,467
Because it might not heal
if we don't air it out.

38
00:02:42,533 --> 00:02:46,767
I'm glad Coach showed
us how to do this.

39
00:02:48,267 --> 00:02:49,267
This won't take long.

40
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:53,300
Does it hurt?

41
00:02:53,367 --> 00:02:54,400
It's okay.

42
00:02:58,767 --> 00:02:59,333
There you go.

43
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,533
The bleeding has stopped.

44
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:04,000
But we still have
to observe it.

45
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:07,067
Thank you.

46
00:03:08,567 --> 00:03:09,667
Don't worry.

47
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:11,667
It will heal soon.

48
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:12,667
I know myself.

49
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:14,633
But we can't afford
to be complacent.

50
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,067
You need to get
your strength back.

51
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:17,700
You can't be weak right now.

52
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:18,500
Stay here, okay?

53
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:20,500
Yen...

54
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,333
wait.

55
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,500
You're panicking again.

56
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:26,067
I don't know what's
going on with me.

57
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:28,467
Ever since we lost Coach,

58
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:31,900
I'm scared
that something might...

59
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:33,600
Nothing will happen to me.

60
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:37,233
This is just a minor wound.

61
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,800
It's nothing.

62
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:41,067
We'll help each other out.

63
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:43,167
We're partners. Okay?

64
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:45,567
Okay, fine.

65
00:03:45,633 --> 00:03:46,633
Just stay here for now.

66
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,067
I'm going to find a way.

67
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:12,033
Hon,

68
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:16,133
I thought you said
you'd stop drinking.

69
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,800
You said you'd make
it up to Red and me.

70
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:19,800
Why?

71
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:23,033
Is he already here?

72
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,833
Did you see him?

73
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:26,933
He's not here!

74
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,200
He's not here.

75
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:33,600
So, Victor, please.

76
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:36,667
Just let me do...

77
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:40,433
what I want to do.

78
00:04:44,167 --> 00:04:46,500
If I were Red, I wouldn't
want to come home if this

79
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:48,300
is what I'm going to see.

80
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:52,567
What did you say?

81
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:55,167
This is really too much, Rina!

82
00:04:55,233 --> 00:04:58,100
You're not the only one
who's having a hard time.

83
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:01,167
You're not the only
one who lost a child!

84
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:04,300
And you're not the only one
missing a child right now!

85
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:08,467
But instead of supporting
each other,

86
00:05:08,533 --> 00:05:09,600
you're getting yourself drunk!

87
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:11,167
Wait!

88
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:12,867
Victor!

89
00:05:12,933 --> 00:05:13,800
Wait!

90
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:17,767
This is how I cope!

91
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,367
I'm still grieving!

92
00:05:22,433 --> 00:05:23,533
And now I'm in so much pain

93
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,800
because of everything
that's going on!

94
00:05:24,867 --> 00:05:26,967
You're so selfish, Rina!

95
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:32,167
It's as if you're the
only one who's hurting!

96
00:05:32,233 --> 00:05:34,367
You're the only
one grieving!

97
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:35,767
Look around you!

98
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,000
At your family!

99
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:42,533
I wanted to give up on this
relationship so many times!

100
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,133
But I stayed for our son,

101
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,800
for Red.

102
00:05:45,867 --> 00:05:47,533
But if he's not coming back
anymore,

103
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:50,500
there's no reason
for us to stay together.

104
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:57,967
Are you actually threatening me
that you're gonna leave me?

105
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:02,600
I'll make it easier for you.

106
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:04,167
I'm leaving you!

107
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:08,067
Rina!

108
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,233
Where are you going?

109
00:06:13,567 --> 00:06:14,500
Rina!

110
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:02,467
What are you doing?

111
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:06,167
Why are you here?

112
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:08,467
You shouldn't strain your wound.

113
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,000
I'm looking for rocks.

114
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,900
Something thin and sharp.

115
00:07:15,967 --> 00:07:18,567
To make a knife.

116
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:20,800
We really need one.

117
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:24,867
That's a good idea!

118
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:27,133
Why didn't we think
of that before?

119
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,100
I don't know.

120
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:32,767
Perhaps we were in shock
about what happened.

121
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:35,633
But after everything
we've been through,

122
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:39,000
I can think clearly now.

123
00:07:39,067 --> 00:07:41,200
I have a lot of ideas now.

124
00:07:44,467 --> 00:07:47,200
So you have to get better soon.

125
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,367
Once you get
your strength back,

126
00:07:48,433 --> 00:07:50,067
we'll start working on our raft.

127
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:52,767
Come on, Yen.

128
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:53,933
I'm all better now.

129
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:56,600
I'm going to help you.

130
00:07:56,667 --> 00:08:00,133
I might be able to
contribute to your ideas.

131
00:08:03,533 --> 00:08:04,867
I'll be right back.

132
00:08:17,267 --> 00:08:18,000
What?

133
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:19,200
Where are you?

134
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:21,400
You're driving
while you're drunk!

135
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,733
Just leave me
alone, Victor!

136
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:28,133
You said you wanted
to leave me, right?

137
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,867
So what do you care?

138
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:32,600
You said you didn't want
to be with me anymore.

139
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:36,933
Did you give up on
finding Red too?

140
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,233
So you don't have to
stay with me anymore?

141
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:41,700
Can you stop?

142
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:43,200
I love our son!

143
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:45,333
And I want to be with him again!

144
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:48,633
I will look for our son.

145
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:52,300
If you don't care
for Red anymore,

146
00:08:52,367 --> 00:08:54,933
I will go and find him myself!

147
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:02,367
Next time, I can go by myself.

148
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:03,400
I can do it myself.

149
00:09:03,467 --> 00:09:06,767
You can't stop living
your life because of me.

150
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:08,267
You're right, Amanda.

151
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:11,367
Even my love life is
getting affected.

152
00:09:11,433 --> 00:09:12,867
What?

153
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:14,033
I'm just kidding.

154
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,367
You know that I don't
have a love life.

155
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:16,500
You're too serious.

156
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:18,667
I'm just trying
to make you smile.

157
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:19,800
Don't worry.

158
00:09:19,867 --> 00:09:22,167
I'll go back to work first
thing in the morning.

159
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,533
You're funny.

160
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:28,967
I'm just worried about you.

161
00:09:29,067 --> 00:09:32,800
Why don't you just wait
for them to call at home?

162
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:35,333
- Wait for an update.
- No, I can't do that.

163
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,833
They need to see the
affected families.

164
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,900
So that they'll do
their job better.

165
00:09:39,967 --> 00:09:42,733
If I need to go there
every day I will until

166
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,733
Yenyen is back with me.

167
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:50,367
Okay, I'll support you
if that's what you want.

168
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:56,933
Amanda?

169
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,067
Amanda...

170
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,733
You ran over Angelo.

171
00:10:06,733 --> 00:10:09,067
Angelo! My son!

172
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:10,600
What happened?

173
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:14,967
What happened to my son?

174
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:18,067
I will do the same to you!

175
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:22,100
An eye for an eye,

176
00:10:22,167 --> 00:10:23,333
Amanda.

177
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:28,800
This is justice.

178
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,833
Wait, Amanda.

179
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,067
I saw someone
welding over there.

180
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:36,100
I'm just going to
check real quick.

181
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:38,500
- Ma'am Josie is looking for...
- Go ahead.

182
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:40,433
- I'll go ahead.
 - for a trolley.

183
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,133
Okay.

184
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:21,567
Amanda!

185
00:11:35,033 --> 00:11:35,833
Yes!

186
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:37,967
Did it work?

187
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:39,500
Yes.

188
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:41,567
You're great, Partner!

189
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:42,467
See?
Here.

190
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:44,667
I have something to
compliment that.

191
00:11:44,733 --> 00:11:45,667
Let me have it.

192
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:47,000
What's that?

193
00:11:47,067 --> 00:11:47,933
You'll see.

194
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:54,300
I see.

195
00:11:54,367 --> 00:11:55,500
That's a good idea, Partner!

196
00:11:55,567 --> 00:11:56,767
You did a good job!

197
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:59,300
Did you think you're the
only one with ideas?

198
00:11:59,367 --> 00:12:00,967
That's good.

199
00:12:01,033 --> 00:12:03,000
Just keep doing that.

200
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:04,167
I'm gonna go make fire.

201
00:12:04,233 --> 00:12:04,733
Stay here, okay?

202
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:06,100
Let me help you.

203
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:08,167
No need.

204
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:09,967
I'm okay. I got it.

205
00:12:10,033 --> 00:12:12,367
I'll make a fire to
keep us warm tonight.

206
00:12:12,433 --> 00:12:13,200
I'll do it myself.

207
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:15,233
- Are you sure?
 - Yes.

208
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:16,400
You might get tired.

209
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:18,233
I got it.

210
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,467
Yen, that's enough.

211
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:35,367
It's about to rain.

212
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:37,033
I'm okay.

213
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:38,433
I almost got it.

214
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,433
You should get some rest.

215
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,767
You've been working all day.

216
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:41,700
Why don't you get some rest?

217
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:43,867
You're the one who's wounded.

218
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:44,833
You're so stubborn.

219
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,933
Can you stop treating
me like a kid?

220
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,000
You're the stubborn one.

221
00:12:51,067 --> 00:12:52,000
You know that I'm right,

222
00:12:52,067 --> 00:12:53,933
but you don't want
to listen to me.

223
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,933
Why are you getting mad at me?

224
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,500
I'm just doing this for us.

225
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:57,500
I know!

226
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:58,967
But that won't happen today.

227
00:12:59,033 --> 00:13:00,700
Don't use up all your energy.

228
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:36,300
We have to go now.

229
00:13:36,367 --> 00:13:39,067
Let's abandon this shelter
and find a new one before

230
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:41,000
the rain gets worse.

231
00:13:41,067 --> 00:13:42,633
- Let's go!
- Come on!

232
00:13:56,033 --> 00:13:57,667
What happened?

233
00:13:57,733 --> 00:13:58,933
Amanda.

234
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,033
Oh no.

235
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,300
Amanda.
Who was that?

236
00:14:06,067 --> 00:14:06,467
Thta's right!

237
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:07,633
Ma'am, wait!

238
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:08,633
- You hit someone.
 - Amanda, wait! Are you okay?
Amanda!

239
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,367
Yes, get her.

240
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:12,767
Those kinds of people
shouldn't be driving!

241
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:13,867
And you!

242
00:14:13,933 --> 00:14:17,000
They shouldn't have let
you get out of prison!

243
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:18,433
You?

244
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:21,267
You're not just a murderer.

245
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:23,400
You are a child murderer!

246
00:14:23,467 --> 00:14:25,100
You killed my son.

247
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:28,467
And the system failed me!

248
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:31,300
So you admit to hitting
my sister with your car!

249
00:14:31,367 --> 00:14:32,967
- You wanted to kill her!
- Hey!

250
00:14:33,033 --> 00:14:34,233
You're a witness, Mister!

251
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,633
You're twisting my words.

252
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:37,067
That's not how it goes!

253
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,500
This woman is a murderer.

254
00:14:38,567 --> 00:14:40,133
She's a murderer!

255
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,633
She should rot in jail!

256
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:44,300
Watch your mouth!

257
00:14:44,367 --> 00:14:46,833
I will have you put in jail
for trying to kill me!

258
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,767
The nerve of you!

259
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:50,233
- Are you drunk?
- You're shameless!

260
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:51,433
You're drunk!

261
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,567
Ma'am, you're drunk.
You reek of alcohol.

262
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:56,067
I'm sorry, but I have to
report you to the police!

263
00:14:56,133 --> 00:14:57,467
I'm not drunk!

264
00:14:57,533 --> 00:14:59,167
I'm not!

265
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,900
Ma'am, please take a seat.

266
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,233
Perhaps you want
to call someone.

267
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,400
You should call your lawyer.

268
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,767
All I want to do is go home.

269
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:10,667
Look, I did nothing wrong.

270
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:13,967
This woman doesn't look
where she's going!

271
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:16,433
And now you're accusing me
of all kinds of things.

272
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:19,633
You're such a liar!

273
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:21,533
She did it on purpose, Sir.

274
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,867
That woman hates me.

275
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:27,100
She told me herself that
she'd get even with me.

276
00:15:27,167 --> 00:15:29,967
Sir, if I tried to run her over,

277
00:15:30,033 --> 00:15:32,033
she should be dead by now.

278
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:34,833
You heard her, right?

279
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:36,500
She wanted to kill me!

280
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:40,333
That's attempted murder.

281
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:43,233
Filing a case against her
won't be that simple.

282
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:46,733
We have to investigate
what happened.

283
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:50,733
So the law favors the
rich over the poor.

284
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:52,200
When you accused me of a crime,

285
00:15:52,267 --> 00:15:54,033
the police came
at once to get me.

286
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,967
And now why does it seem like...

287
00:15:56,033 --> 00:15:56,600
Ma'am...

288
00:15:56,667 --> 00:15:57,767
you were afraid of...

289
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,133
- What are you going to do?
- Ma'am.

290
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:02,967
How dare you even
compare yourself to me?

291
00:16:03,033 --> 00:16:04,133
Please!

292
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:29,433
Let me see that.

293
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,367
I think you strained
your wounded leg.

294
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:43,667
Let me help you.

295
00:17:03,033 --> 00:17:03,633
Is it okay?
Yes.

296
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:08,167
That's good.

297
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:16,500
Thank you.

298
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,967
I'm sorry about earlier.

299
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,200
I'm just worried about you.

300
00:17:22,267 --> 00:17:23,500
I don't want you
to tire yourself.

301
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:25,767
Hey.

302
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:29,300
We have nothing else
to do here but rest.

303
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:30,233
Don't worry.

304
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:38,133
I think this place is safe
for us to stay the night.

305
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,433
Let's stay here for now.

306
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:42,567
It's cold.

307
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,400
Sir,

308
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:52,333
that woman is a murderer.

309
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:55,600
She killed my son!

310
00:17:57,367 --> 00:18:00,367
I'm the victim here.

311
00:18:00,433 --> 00:18:03,267
I lost a child because of her!

312
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:06,633
She should go to jail, not me!

313
00:18:10,033 --> 00:18:11,667
I didn't do anything wrong.

314
00:18:13,633 --> 00:18:14,633
So I'm leaving.

315
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:16,267
Ma'am, you can't leave.

316
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:18,867
She might not file a case
of attempted murder against you.

317
00:18:18,933 --> 00:18:22,400
But you were driving under
the influence of alcohol.

318
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:24,800
And you hurt someone.

319
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:28,133
She can file a case of physical
injuries against you.

320
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,567
Me?

321
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,000
She's going to file
a case against me?

322
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:31,733
No! That can't happen!

323
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,733
You should go to jail, Amanda!

324
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,533
You should go to jail!

325
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:37,767
Well, will you look at that?

326
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:39,200
You wanted to hurt me.

327
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:41,933
But you put yourself
in harm's way instead.

328
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:42,833
What now?

329
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:46,133
What goes around comes around!

330
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,600
You're a monster!

331
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:50,333
Beast!

332
00:18:52,467 --> 00:18:53,433
Let go of me!

333
00:18:59,167 --> 00:19:03,033
Tomorrow I'm going to
look for fruits to eat.

334
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:08,767
I'll also look for an
area with a lot of fish.

335
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:09,733
Are you going fishing?

336
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,967
Yes, it's easy.

337
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:13,233
I already have an idea.

338
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:19,833
I'm not being picky,
but we don't have a fire.

339
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:21,067
How are we going
to eat that?

340
00:19:21,133 --> 00:19:23,933
We might get sick
if we eat raw fish.

341
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,500
We can dry it up under the sun.

342
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:27,200
Dried fish!

343
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:31,300
Aunt Dindi used to
do that a lot before.

344
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:39,133
You know what...

345
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:42,300
we should stay here.

346
00:19:42,367 --> 00:19:44,600
It will be easier to
make a fire in here.

347
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:46,767
It's not windy here.

348
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:50,233
You're always
doing everything.

349
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:52,100
Are you that independent?

350
00:19:54,733 --> 00:19:55,800
Yes.

351
00:19:57,467 --> 00:20:01,367
My mom taught me how to do
things when I was young.

352
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:04,133
Because my Aunt Dindi
has school

353
00:20:04,233 --> 00:20:06,267
and my mom has to go to work.

354
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:08,567
So I know how to do
things on my own.

355
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:12,067
What about your dad?

356
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:13,400
He's gone.

357
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:16,000
He got in an accident
when I was still a baby.

358
00:20:17,733 --> 00:20:24,667
But my aunt told me he abandoned
us long before he died.

359
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:31,300
I'm sorry for bringing that up.

360
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:32,800
Don't worry,

361
00:20:32,867 --> 00:20:34,733
I'm not like him.

362
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,567
I will never leave you.

363
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:39,733
We'll help each other out
because we're partners.

364
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:42,633
But you're wounded.

365
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,700
It's okay. I can do it myself.

366
00:20:44,767 --> 00:20:48,867
So you don't need my help?

367
00:20:48,933 --> 00:20:50,233
No.

368
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:52,300
Really?

369
00:20:52,367 --> 00:20:53,500
Yes.

370
00:20:56,367 --> 00:20:57,833
Really?

371
00:20:57,900 --> 00:20:58,867
- Yes.
- Even if...

372
00:21:00,467 --> 00:21:02,367
- Even if...
- What?

373
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:04,500
Even if there's
a spider on your nape?

374
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:05,267
What spider?

375
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,633
Where? Get it!

376
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:08,733
Get it off!

377
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,300
- Red, please!
- It's big!

378
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:10,833
- It's scary.
- Red!

379
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:12,067
Get it off!

380
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:13,100
It's climbing up!

381
00:21:13,167 --> 00:21:14,200
Get it off! Hurry! Red!

382
00:21:14,267 --> 00:21:16,433
It's on your head now!

383
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:17,800
- Get it off!
- It's so big!

384
00:21:17,867 --> 00:21:18,700
Get it off!

385
00:21:18,767 --> 00:21:20,600
Red! Get it off!

386
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:24,167
Don't move!

387
00:21:24,233 --> 00:21:25,200
Here you go!

388
00:21:25,267 --> 00:21:28,267
What are you doing?

389
00:21:30,733 --> 00:21:32,900
That hurts.

390
00:21:32,967 --> 00:21:35,400
Fine, I deserve that.

391
00:21:35,467 --> 00:21:37,867
I just wanted to prove to you

392
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:40,933
that you will need help too.

393
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,167
That you can't do all
things on your own.

394
00:21:46,733 --> 00:21:47,900
Don't worry.

395
00:21:47,967 --> 00:21:50,233
If there's a real spider on you,
I will save you for real.

396
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:51,233
Come on, smile.

397
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:52,933
Frowning doesn't suit you.

398
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,200
You look prettier
when you're smiling.

399
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,033
There you go.

400
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:09,933
Why are you being like this?

401
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:16,333
You're still good to me
even though I'm the reason

402
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:18,700
you got wounded.

403
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:24,233
Is that why you're acting like
that since earlier because

404
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:25,500
you feel guilty?

405
00:22:27,833 --> 00:22:30,800
I should always think
of our situation.

406
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:34,400
We only have each other.

407
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:38,333
No one can get hurt.

408
00:22:39,933 --> 00:22:41,767
Yen,

409
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:44,100
I'm not blaming
you for what happened.

410
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:51,933
Partners help each other out.

411
00:22:52,033 --> 00:22:54,033
We don't blame each other.

412
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:55,267
And...

413
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:59,733
don't worry about my wound.

414
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:00,700
It's a minor wound.

415
00:23:00,767 --> 00:23:02,767
It'll probably get
better tomorrow.

416
00:23:02,833 --> 00:23:04,533
Don't worry.

417
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:07,167
So, you should smile.

418
00:23:16,667 --> 00:23:17,767
Ma'am, everything
is taken care of.

419
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:20,100
We'll give you an
update about the case.

420
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:22,333
We'll make sure that Mrs. Ramos
will get detained

421
00:23:22,433 --> 00:23:23,100
the whole night.

422
00:23:23,167 --> 00:23:24,267
I'm glad to hear that.

423
00:23:24,333 --> 00:23:25,167
Let's go, Amanda.

424
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,600
Hey! Get me out of here!

425
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:28,333
I know my rights!

426
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:29,900
Hey, you! Ugly woman!

427
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:32,633
Did you really think you won?

428
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:33,767
Do you think we're now even?

429
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:34,567
No!

430
00:23:35,633 --> 00:23:36,700
Hey.

431
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:40,267
You can never call it quits.

432
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:43,433
What you're going through
right now is not enough

433
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:47,100
for all the time you stole
from my daughter and me!

434
00:23:47,167 --> 00:23:48,733
And one more thing,

435
00:23:50,133 --> 00:23:51,400
I'm innocent.

436
00:23:51,467 --> 00:23:54,100
That's why they released
me from prison.

437
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:56,867
If there's a criminal
between us, it's you!

438
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:58,200
- Really?
- Yes, really.

439
00:23:58,267 --> 00:24:00,167
Do not celebrate just yet!

440
00:24:00,233 --> 00:24:01,267
Hey!

441
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:03,600
I'll be out of here soon!

442
00:24:03,667 --> 00:24:05,233
You better be ready!

443
00:24:05,300 --> 00:24:07,967
You're a monster, Amanda!

444
00:24:08,033 --> 00:24:10,233
Get me out of here!

445
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:12,433
I know my rights!

446
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:13,467
Get me out of here!

447
00:25:00,633 --> 00:25:01,500
Yenyen.

448
00:25:02,867 --> 00:25:03,933
Yenyen.

449
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:05,800
Yen.

450
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:09,400
Yenyen, wake up.

451
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:10,467
Why?

452
00:25:10,533 --> 00:25:11,767
Yen, there's a...

453
00:25:13,100 --> 00:25:14,367
there's a snake.

454
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,767
Are you messing with me, Red?

455
00:25:17,833 --> 00:25:19,033
Yen, I'm not kidding.

456
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:21,467
Yenyen, there's really a snake.

457
00:25:21,533 --> 00:25:22,767
Wake up, please.

458
00:25:27,667 --> 00:25:28,467
Get up slowly!

459
00:25:30,533 --> 00:25:31,533
There it is.

460
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:44,667
We'll fix this.

461
00:25:44,733 --> 00:25:47,533
But it's too late to
bail her out today.

462
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:49,200
She won't be out until tomorrow.

463
00:25:49,267 --> 00:25:52,467
Attorney, if she has to spend
the night in jail

464
00:25:52,533 --> 00:25:55,300
to learn her lesson, so be it.

465
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:57,433
We should have filed an
attempted murder case

466
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:58,667
against that woman!

467
00:25:58,733 --> 00:26:02,067
So she'll rot in jail without
being able to make bail.

468
00:26:02,133 --> 00:26:05,867
I just want to let her know
that I won't back down.

469
00:26:05,933 --> 00:26:07,833
Victor had enough.

470
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:10,100
And I don't want him to know
that we're doing

471
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,467
anything against that woman.

472
00:26:11,533 --> 00:26:13,700
This is the first time you kept
something from your husband.

473
00:26:13,767 --> 00:26:16,233
Victor doesn't even know
about our business.

474
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:17,967
Better keep it that way!

475
00:26:18,033 --> 00:26:20,333
She only got
out of prison.

476
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:23,700
But not from the hell
I'm about to give her!

477
00:26:23,767 --> 00:26:28,533
I heard you're keeping an
ex-convict on my property!

478
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:29,833
Is that true?

479
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:32,567
Wait, let me explain.

480
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:33,867
I want you out of here!

481
00:26:33,933 --> 00:26:35,167
Right now!

482
00:26:35,233 --> 00:26:36,067
Get out!
